@Raven Rock. 
Can you point to an example of that please. I’m intrigued. I’m curious to know if there are perforations in the upright L part near the top to allow additional air to mix in? 
It’s one of those topics that is easy to over engineer (because one thinks one knows something) but really the simple solution like you’ve described is the best.

@ravenrock541 that’s a lot of passion you have right there to write so much. I appreciate the time and information. I suspect you are a combustion nerd like myself. I’m personally still really impressed with the pizza oven dome shaped combustion chamber. Anyway, I’ll have to get myself a low cost welder and actually make an L Rocket Stove to really see it in action. I hear you about smoke and neighbours. Not a good combination. 
Do share the pic please. Measurements too if it’s feasible. 
Thanks again for the reply.
